Introduction

Noh Jihyeon, known under her stage name Jiana, is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper, and dancer under BEATS Entertainment and DSP Media. She is best known as the main vocalist, visual, and center of the girl group YOUNG POSSE.

On October 18, 2023, Jiana officially debuted with YOUNG POSSE with the mini album "MACARONI CHEESE EP".

When Jiana was 13, she moved to Seoul where she grew up. She began training at 14, having previously been a trainee at Source Music and Fantagio, before passing her Beats Entertainment audition in 2021.
